Package: monecascale
Title: Scalable Backends for MONECA Mobility Clustering
Description: Provides scalable clustering backends for the moneca package,
    including hierarchical degree-corrected stochastic block model
    (DC-SBM) inference via moneca_sbm(), bipartite / rectangular
    clustering via moneca_bipartite(), and post-hoc hierarchy-level
    auto-selection via auto_segment_levels() (MDL elbow or mutual
    information plateau). Version 0.3.0 adds auto_segment_levels() for
    automatic stopping-rule selection from fully-fitted hierarchies.
    Designed as a sibling package that extends moneca beyond
    classification-scale mobility matrices while reusing moneca's output
    contract and downstream analysis / plotting stack. The load-bearing
    theoretical observation is that moneca's relative-risk matrix RR =
    O / E is the DC-SBM residual under identity block interaction, so
    SBM inference is a principled scalable drop-in for the
    clique-enumeration step. For two-mode (rectangular) data,
    moneca_bipartite() extends this to the degree-corrected Latent Block
    Model (DcLbm) on scaled-rounded RR.
Version: 0.3.0
